180 TEST_F(ProtobufTsdfTest, LayerSubsetSerializationToFile) {
181  const std::string file = "subset_layer_test_1.tsdf.voxblox";
182 
183  BlockIndexList block_index_list;
184  BlockIndex block_index_1 = {-4, 5, 0};
185  block_index_list.push_back(block_index_1);
186  BlockIndex block_index_4 = {3, -1, -2};
187  block_index_list.push_back(block_index_4);
188 
189  constexpr bool kIncludeAllBlocks = false;
190 
191  io::SaveLayerSubset(*layer_, file, block_index_list, kIncludeAllBlocks);
192 
193  Layer<TsdfVoxel>::Ptr layer_from_file;
194  ASSERT_TRUE(io::LoadLayer<TsdfVoxel>(file, &layer_from_file));
195 
196  // Remove all other blocks for comparison.
197  BlockIndexList all_block_indices;
198  layer_->getAllAllocatedBlocks(&all_block_indices);
199  for (const BlockIndex& index : all_block_indices) {
200  if (index != block_index_1 && index != block_index_4) {
201  layer_->removeBlock(index);
202  }
203  }
204 
205  CompareLayers(*layer_, *layer_from_file);
206 }

208 // Save the example layer to file, and prepare another layer with 4 existing
209 // blocks. Load all the blocks from the example layer file into layer and
210 // compare.
211 TEST_F(ProtobufTsdfTest, LayerSubsetSerializationFromFile) {
212  const std::string file = "subset_layer_test_2.tsdf.voxblox";
213 
214  io::SaveLayer(*layer_, file);
215 
216  // These are the existing blocks in the layer
217  BlockIndexList block_index_list;
218  BlockIndex block_index_1 = {-4000, 5000, 0};
219  block_index_list.push_back(block_index_1);
220  BlockIndex block_index_2 = {-7000, 2000, 1000};
221  block_index_list.push_back(block_index_2);
222  BlockIndex block_index_3 = {3000, 0, 9000};
223  block_index_list.push_back(block_index_3);
224  BlockIndex block_index_4 = {3000, -1000, -2000};
225  block_index_list.push_back(block_index_4);
226 
227  Layer<TsdfVoxel> layer_with_blocks_from_file(voxel_size_, voxels_per_side_);
228  layer_with_blocks_from_file.allocateNewBlock(block_index_1);
229  layer_with_blocks_from_file.allocateNewBlock(block_index_2);
230  layer_with_blocks_from_file.allocateNewBlock(block_index_3);
231  layer_with_blocks_from_file.allocateNewBlock(block_index_4);
232 
233  // Now load the blocks from the file layer and add it.
234  ASSERT_TRUE(io::LoadBlocksFromFile<TsdfVoxel>(
235  file, Layer<TsdfVoxel>::BlockMergingStrategy::kProhibit,
236  &layer_with_blocks_from_file));
237 
238  // Add those blocks to the layer for comparison.
239  layer_->allocateNewBlock(block_index_1);
240  layer_->allocateNewBlock(block_index_2);
241  layer_->allocateNewBlock(block_index_3);
242  layer_->allocateNewBlock(block_index_4);
243 
244  CompareLayers(*layer_, layer_with_blocks_from_file);
245 }

247 TEST_F(ProtobufTsdfTest, MultipleLayerSerialization) {

249  // Match TSDF settings.
250  esdf_layer.reset(new Layer<EsdfVoxel>(voxel_size_, voxels_per_side_));
251  voxblox::test::SetUpTestLayer(kBlockVolumeDiameter, esdf_layer.get());
252 
253  voxblox::test::LayerTest<EsdfVoxel> esdf_test;
254 
255  const std::string file = "multi_layer_test.voxblox";
256  bool clear_file = true;
257  io::SaveLayer(*layer_, file, clear_file);
258  clear_file = false;
259  io::SaveLayer(*esdf_layer, file, clear_file);
260 
261  constexpr bool multiple_layer_support = true;
262  Layer<TsdfVoxel>::Ptr tsdf_layer_from_file;
263  ASSERT_TRUE(io::LoadLayer<TsdfVoxel>(file, multiple_layer_support,
264  &tsdf_layer_from_file));
265 
266  Layer<EsdfVoxel>::Ptr esdf_layer_from_file;
267  ASSERT_TRUE(io::LoadLayer<EsdfVoxel>(file, multiple_layer_support,
268  &esdf_layer_from_file));
269 
270  CompareLayers(*layer_, *tsdf_layer_from_file);
271  esdf_test.CompareLayers(*esdf_layer, *esdf_layer_from_file);
272 }
